[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Mena-asia_default_banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Itoigawa"]}," (",{"type":"{{","value":[["lang"],["ja"],["糸魚川"]]},") is a city in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Niigata (prefecture)"],["Niigata prefecture"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\n\nItoigawa is situated at the northern terminus of the great fault line, the Itoigawa-Shizuoka Tectonic Line geologically separating North-Eastern Japan and South-Western Japan.\n\nThe region includes the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Itoigawa Geopark"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\nItoigawa is located on the JR West  ",{"type":"'''","value":["Hokuriku Main Line"]}," between ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Joetsu"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Toyama"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\nThe closest airport to the Itoigawa is ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Toyama"],["Toyama Airport"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\n\nFrom ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tokyo"]]}," Station, Itoigawa can be reached by taking the Joetsu Shinkansen (",{"type":"''","value":["Tanigawa, Max Tanigawa, Toki or Max Toki"]},") to Echigo-Yuzawa (越後湯沢) and then transferring to the ",{"type":"''","value":["Hakutaka"]}," (はくたか) limited express train for the run to Itoigawa. This ride lasts about 2 hours 45 minutes with a good connection in Echigo-Yuzawa, and it costs ¥9830 each way. ",{"type":"'''","value":["Japan Rail Pass"]}," holders have to pay ¥1450 each way for the portion of the trip between Echigo-Yuzawa and Naoetsu, which is operated by Hokuetsu Railway. The ",{"type":"'''","value":["JR East Rail Pass"]}," covers the Echigo-Yuzawa - Naoetsu segment, but does not cover the portion onward to Itoigawa; the full fare must be paid (¥1690).\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Fossa Magna Museum"],["alt=フォッサマグナミュージアム"],["url="],["email="],["address=1313 Ichinomiya"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone =+81  25-553-1880"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours=9am-4:30pm"],["price=Adults ¥500, Students ¥300"],["content= Minerals and fossils dug up from fossa magna plates are on display at this  museum."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Itoigawa Geopark"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/geo-itoigawa.com\/eng\/"],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=A group of sites in the immediate environs of Itoigawa. It is part of the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["UNESCO Global Geoparks Network"]]},"."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Connect"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Itoigawa tourist association Information centre"],["url="],["email=itokan@world.ocn.ne.jp"],["address=1-7-11 Omachi"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone =+81  25-552-1742"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["routebox"],["image1=JR Hokuriku icon.png"],["imagesize1=100"],["directionl1=W"],["majorl1=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kanazawa"]]}],["minorl1=",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Toyama"]]}]}],["directionr1=E"],["majorr1= ",{"type":"[[","value":[["image:JR Shin-etsu icon.png"],["75px"]]}," ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Nagaoka"],["E"]]}],["minorr1=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Joetsu"]]}],["image2=Hokuriku Expwy Route Sign.svg"],["imagesize2=100"],["directionl2=W"],["majorl2=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kanazawa"]]}],["minorl2=",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Toyama"]]}]}],["directionr2=E"],["majorr2=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Niigata"]]}],["minorr2=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Joetsu"]]}]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value"